# HoneyHive Semantic Conventions

The canonical `honeyhive.*` attribute names that the HoneyHive ingestion
pipeline accepts. This site is the public reference for SDK authors,
integration partners, and customers building on HoneyHive's OTLP
endpoint.

Every attribute on this site has a stability tier — **stable**
attributes are safe to depend on long-term, **development** attributes
may change before a major release. The wire-format names defined here
are the contract between SDK emitters, OTLP ingestion, and the
HoneyHive product UI.

## Browse the registry

- [**Attributes**](attributes/) — the full reference, organised by namespace.

## How this site is generated

This documentation is rendered from machine-readable YAML in the
[`honeyhiveai/semantic-conventions`](https://github.com/honeyhiveai/semantic-conventions)
GitHub repository using [weaver](https://github.com/open-telemetry/weaver),
the OpenTelemetry-blessed CLI for semantic-convention registries. Edits
to attribute definitions land via pull request; on merge to `main` this
site is republished automatically.

